					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="4r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>The second derash in Leviticus 10:16 is, contrary to the rule, not placed at the beginning of the line. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>70 membranes, 268 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>463/760</height>
										<width>3422</width>
									</dimensions>
									</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>70 membranes, with wooden rollers. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Roller handle broken but attached to scroll. </p>
									<p>Very occasional stains, wax, etc. </p>
									<p>Occasional and slight mould mottling on verso.  </p>
									<p>Ink flaky in places. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="268" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stiching. </p>
									<p>268 columns in total, three to five columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהיק, sometimes also ו and ח (which is occasionally arched). </p>
									<p>Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>Special shapes of the letter  נ, פ and broken ו occur. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah. </p>
									<p>Wooden rollers (760mm high). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
